Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potato chunks and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside for now.

Meanwhile, pop the @Panko breadcrumbs{25%grams}, @fresh pesto{32%grams} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb into a #small bowl{} and mix together.

Lay the @basa fillets{2} onto a lined baking tray.

Spoon the pesto crumb evenly over the fish, pressing it down with the back of the #spoon{}.

Pop the basa on the top shelf and the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven to cook until the veg is tender and the fish is cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Buttery Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and allow it to evaporate, ~{1-2%mins}.

Pour in the @water{100%ml} for the sauce and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, then bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%mins}. Vigorously stir in the @butter{30%grams} for the sauce until melted, then take off the heat.

== Mash ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @?butter{a knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with salt and @ground black pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Serve the basa with the mash and roasted broccoli alongside, then spoon over the buttery sauce to finish.

> Enjoy!